result.name: Tom N Toms Coffee

reviews.text: Great selection of coffees, a bit cheaper than the Starbucks one level up, and also unlimited free wifi, and not limited to 30 minutes as for Starbucks
better than starbucks but still ordinary coffee but great mustard honey sauce ham toast!

I actually think that them being here is a very good move, although it's a little secluded from the rest of the Times Square. It's located on the 8th floor, at the main shopping area. There's quite a lack of good coffee places here, especially given how crowded Times Square can be on both weekdays and weekends. Do try the honey cold brew and the pumpkin latte - they're pretty uniquely flavored.
Cosy place for great 'real' coffee in Times Square. We also had the garlic toast with syrup which was delicious.
Strategic place to wait for my wife and daughter while they go shopping.
